According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), more than one-third (36.5%) of American adults have obesity, which is significantly higher than the rates in Ohio (29.4%), Michigan (30.5%), or Toun (27.5%). Additionally, the prevalence of dance clubs in the United States is also higher compared to other options, making it the best choice.
